HEADWORD: Clockwork
<hw>Clock"work`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
machinery of a clock, or machinery resembling that of a clock; machinery
which produces regularity of movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

